    "body": "\r\n  This PR works around a ROCm-specific `tvm-ffi` / `torch-c-dlpack-ext` tensor marshalling issue in TileLang.\r\n\r\n  On ROCm, the torch C DLPack fast path can corrupt tensor metadata when TileLang calls generated TVM FFI kernels. This shows up as packed API errors such as:\r\n\r\n  ```text\r\n  ndim expected 2, but got 512\r\n  ```\r\n  The root issue is likely in the ROCm path of `torch-c-dlpack-ext` or `tvm-ffi` tensor exchange, not in individual TileLang kernels. This PR does not fix that dependency-level bug; it avoids the broken path inside TileLang.\r\n\r\n  ## Changes\r\n\r\n  - Disable the torch C DLPack loader on ROCm during TileLang import.\r\n  - For ROCm FP8 tensors, export the byte view through DLPack and restore the expected TileLang dtype with _create_view.\r\n  - Simplify atomic test reference computation from Python GPU scalar loops to A.sum(dim=0).\r\n\r\n  ## Testing\r\n\r\n  - ROCm CI passed:\r\n    Test for Python 3.12 with Nightly-ROCm-7.2\r\n  - Local ROCm-equivalent test run:\r\n    664 passed, 540 skipped",
    "created_at": "2026-05-11T06:26:28Z",
